Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automatic speech recognition and natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper deals with audio data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a framework that involves training machine learning models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with developing an AI system for speech recognition. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possibility as the paper uses a sequence-of-sequence autoencoder for feature extraction.
